; DBPS v1.0 Section 5 — Path Addressing Formal Grammar
;
; Defines the syntax of knowledge entry paths in the DimensionalBase Protocol.
; All conformant implementations MUST accept paths matching this grammar and
; MUST reject paths that do not match.
;
; Reference: RFC 5234 (ABNF)

path            = segment *( "/" segment )

segment         = 1*segment-char

segment-char    = ALPHA / DIGIT / "-" / "_" / "."

; Patterns extend paths with wildcards (used in get(), subscribe(), ACL)

pattern         = pattern-seg *( "/" pattern-seg )

pattern-seg     = segment / "*" / "**"

; "*" matches exactly one segment (does not cross "/" boundaries)
; "**" matches zero or more segments (crosses "/" boundaries)

; Examples:
;   "task/auth/status"    — valid path
;   "task/**"             — valid pattern (matches task, task/auth, task/auth/jwt, ...)
;   "task/*/status"       — valid pattern (matches task/auth/status, task/deploy/status)
;   "task/ auth"          — INVALID (space in segment)
;   "../etc/passwd"       — INVALID (.. not allowed)
;   ""                    — INVALID (empty path)

; Constraints (not expressible in ABNF):
;   - Maximum path length: 512 characters
;   - No null bytes (U+0000)
;   - No directory traversal ("..") segments
;   - Segments are case-sensitive
